news.title: Single family housing starts in USA drops by 12.4% in March 2024
news.para: The report from the Commerce Department on Tuesday also showed permits for future construction of single-family houses fell to a five-month low.

news.title: Home prices in UK drop by 0.2% in February 2024
news.para: The ONS also said its gauge of private rents rose by 9.2% in the year to March - the biggest increase since records started in 2015 and up from 9.0% in the 12 months to February.

news.title: China's Zhengzhou city tells state-owned company to buy second-hand homes
news.para: Local state state-owned company Zhengzhou Urban Development Group Co. will buy 500 second-hand homes from April 20 to June 30, according to a notice released by the Zhengzhou Real Estate Association on Monday.

news.title: Over 46% office space leases in India by offshoring industry: Report
news.para: India's offshoring market dominates office space leasing, comprising 46% of total leasing in 2023, led by global capability centers (GCCs).

news.title: Upload permit information to curb illegal sand transport: Bombay HC
news.para: The high court also ordered the directorate of mines and geology (DMG) to publish on its website a list of permits that have already been issued for the transportation of sand in Goa and are currently valid. The HC said the list will help spot illegalities.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC issues notices to five contractors executing metro projects over pending property tax
news.para: ​​​In a release, the Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation (BMC) said final notices for making payment in seven days have been issued to these companies for non-payment of property tax.

news.title: Kanodia Group acquires 1.74-acre land in Gurugram for Rs 153 crore
news.para: Gautam Kanodia, co-founder of Kanodia Group said, "We plan to generate revenue in excess of Rs 1,000 crore from this project. The project is scheduled to be launched by the end of this year and is expected to be completed within 48 to 60 months."

news.title: Construction sites in Ahmedabad must use dust sensors to check pollution
news.para: “The real-time feed from the dust sensors and CCTVs should be relayed to the AMC’s Smart City control and command centre,” said a senior AMC official.

news.title: Brigade Enterprises reports 46% increase in sales bookings in FY24
news.para: In a statement, Brigade Enterprises said it has achieved pre-sales of Rs 6,013 crore in FY24 and Rs 2,243 crore in the fourth quarter of FY24 - the highest ever for both in terms of a quarter as well as financial year.

news.title: Sunteck Realty posts 20% rise in sale bookings in FY24
news.para: According to a regulatory filing, Sunteck Realty sale bookings increased 26 per cent to Rs 678 crore in the fourth quarter of last fiscal from Rs 537 crore in the corresponding period of the 2022-23 fiscal.

news.title: Dubai's high-end property sales rise on overseas demand
news.para: A total of 105 homes worth an overall $1.73 billion were sold from January to March, up from around $1.6 billion a year earlier, according to property consultancy Knight Frank.

news.title: PWC rejects allegations over China Evergrande Group’s audit
news.para: Accounting firm PwC on Monday rejected an anonymous letter that criticised the company's involvement in auditing beleaguered Chinese real estate giant Evergrande, saying the letter contained "false allegations".

news.title: Homebuilder confidence in USA holds steady in April
news.para: Measures of current sales and prospective buyer traffic both ticked up to their highest levels since August while the survey's measure of sales in the next six months slipped.

news.title: New home prices in China drop by 2.2% in March
news.para: New home prices in March dropped 2.2% from a year earlier, marking the biggest decline since August 2015, and worse than a 1.4% fall in February, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data.

news.title: Punjab and Haryana HC stays all constructions in green belts of Sirsa
news.para: The main allegations are that local political leaders, including Gopal Kanda and his brother Gobind Kanda, have been supporting the encroachments through their political clout.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body offers paid pickup service for C&D waste
news.para: Citizens can visit GHMC website online services construction & demolition waste pick up service request, My GHMC app or toll-free number.

news.title: South Goa district magistrate asks owners to verify tenants properly
news.para: The magistrate has directed that the verification must be carried out through proof of identity such as election card, driving licence, Aadhaar card, passport, etc.
